-- Ex-Sparx Chief Operating Officer Joins Goldman Sachs Asset
-- B y   T o m o k o   Y a m a z a k i
-- 2012-05-14T08:00:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-14/ex-sparx-chief-operating-officer-joins-goldman-sachs-asset.html
Masaki Taniguchi, a former executive
at  Sparx Group Co. (8739) , has rejoined Goldman Sachs Asset Management
in Hong Kong as the head of product development in the Asia-
Pacific region, according to an internal memo obtained by
Bloomberg News.  Edward Naylor, a Hong Kong-based spokesman for Goldman
Sachs Group Inc., confirmed the content of the memo.  Taniguchi, based in Hong Kong, rejoined Goldman Sachs Asset
Management after being with Tokyo-based Sparx for a decade,
according to the memo. Prior to Sparx, he worked for Goldman
Sachs Asset Management in Japan, where he served in various
roles, including strategic planning and institutional marketing.  In March 2011, Taniguchi was appointed as the group chief
operating officer at Sparx and relocated to  Hong Kong  from  Tokyo 
as the Japanese asset manager planned to expand its business in
Asia.  To contact the reporter on this story:
